Dr. Ehud Ur, Professor of Medicine at Dalhousie University in Halifax, Nova Scotia, and Chairman of the Department of Clinic and Science of the Canadian Diabetes Association, pointed out that the research work is still in its infancy.
Like some other experts, he expressed skepticism about whether it is possible to cure diabetes, and pointed out that the findings would have no significance for people who already suffered from type 1 diabetes.
On Monday, Sara Danius, the Permanent Secretary of the Swedish Academy's Nobel Prize in Literature Committee, announced on Sveriges Radio in Sweden that the committee had ceased its efforts to inform Bob Dylan about his Nobel Prize in Literature honor, after it had failed to reach him personally.
Danius said, "At the moment we are not doing anything. I have called his closest associate and sent him emails and received very friendly responses. That is enough for now."
