While an experimental vaccine appears to be able to reduce Ebola mortality, so far there are no drugs that have been proven to be clearly suitable for treating existing infections.
An antibody cocktail, ZMapp, initially proved promising, however formal studies showed that, in terms of preventing deaths, it brought fewer benefits than hoped.
In the PALM study, ZMapp served as a control, i.e. the scientists used it as a baseline and compared the three other treatments with it.
USA Gymnastics supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and accepts it as an absolute necessity that the Olympic family advocates for a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the USOC's statement that the interests of our athletes and clubs and their sport are better served if we drive meaningful changes within our organization, rather than proceeding with a decertification.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could reveal how abuse on the scale described so bravely by the survivors of Larry Nassar could remain undetected for so long, and welcomes all necessary and appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal - to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible for athletes, so they can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive, and self-determined environment.
