The 802.11n standard operates on the frequencies 2.4 Ghz and 5.0 Ghz.
This allows it to be backwards compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b, and 802.11g, provided the base station has dual-radio.
The speed of 802.11 n is significantly faster than its predecessors, which had a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbit/s.
